sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1688001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The genes responsible for producing the mono-rhamnolipids (biosurfactant) are called RhlA and RhlB. The protein encoded by these two genes make up the subunits of rhamnosyltransferase I. The RhlA gene (BBa_K1688002) codes for a 3-(hydroxyalkanoyloxy) alkanoic acid (HAA) fatty acid tail and the RhlB (BBa_K1688003) connects this tail to a rhamnose molecule making a mono-rhamnolipid. The biobrick BBa_K1688001 is a composite part of BBa_K1688002 and BBa_K1688003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Biosurfers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1688002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The enzymes responsible for producing the mono-rhamnolipids (biosurfactant) are called RhlA and RhlB. The mono- rhamnolipids consist of a hydrophobic tail and a hydrophilic head. The RhlA gene codes for the fatty acid tail and it has been lifted and improved by iGEM10 tokyo-NoKoGen and iGEM14 Nankai from pseudomona aeruginosa. The biobrick from team Nankai BBa_K1331001 consists of gene RhlA whereas the biobrick BBa_K1688002 consist of a ribosomal binding site and a gene coding RhlA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Biosurfers
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: RhlA was lifted from 2015 DNA distribution kit and assembled with RBS

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1688003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The genes responsible for producing mono-rhamnolipids (biosurfactant) are called RhlA and RhlB.. The mono- rhamnolipids consist of a hydrophilic rhamnose head and a 3-(hydroxyalkanoyloxy) alkanoic acid (HAA) fatty acid tail. The RhlA gene (BBa_K1688002) codes for the fatty acid tail and the RhlB connects the tail to a rhamnose molecule. The RhlB gene has been lifted and improved by iGEM10 tokyo-NoKoGen and iGEM14 Nankai from pseudomona aeruginosa. The biobrick BBa_K1688003 is an assembly of RBS with BBa_K1331004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Biosurfers
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The RhlA gene (BBa_K1331004) and RBS ((BBa_B0034) was lifted from 2015 DNA Distribution Kit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1331004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Modified rhlB coding sequence from Pseudomonas aeruginosa SQ6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RhlB together with RhlA encodes Rhamnosyltransferase I for mono-rahmnolipids biosynthesis in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. This part includes bp upstream noncoding gene and bp downstreanm gene of RhlB. Two mutations have been done to remove the PstI restriction sites contained in the coding sequence, which won't change the amino acid sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianyi Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Two mutations have been done to remove the PstI restriction sites contained in the coding sequence, which won't change the amino acid sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
